Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.65,sign_2314_1_To_think_the_Gui,Text,0000,0000,0000,,To think the Guild would send \Nme a challenge request.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:04.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,To think the Guild would send \Nme a challenge request.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.85,0:00:07.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,This'll stave off my boredom a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.48,sign_2459_4_To_Edogawa_Rampo,Text,0000,0000,0000,,To Edogawa Rampo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.48,sign_2459_5_Invitation_for_a,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Invitation for a Detective Game
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:10.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Though I suspect it's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_7_Welcome__Rampo_k,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Rampo-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_8_A_is_B,Text,0000,0000,0000,,A is B
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_9_A_is_not_B,Text,0000,0000,0000,,A is not B
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.61,0:00:14.45,sign_2532_10_Fill_in_A_and_B_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Fill in A and B so that both \Nhold true, and enter the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:14.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he wants you to fill in the blanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.78,0:00:17.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I have any idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.66,0:00:22.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Yosano-san, do you have a pen?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:31.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the mastermind who \Nthought to challenge me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:38.55,sign_3043_15_Guild_Chief_Arch,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Chief Architect\N of the Guild\N E. A. Poe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:38.55,sign_3043_16_Ability__Black_C,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: Black Cat in \Nthe Rue Morgue
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:35.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Were you been able to solve \Nthe riddle at the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.55,0:00:44.10,sign_2532_10_Fill_in_A_and_B_2,,0000,0000,0000,,This sentence is five words.\N\NThis sentence is not five words.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.52,0:00:43.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I'd expect no less from my \Nworthy opponent, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.52,0:00:47.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's my turn to ask a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.19,0:00:51.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.93,0:00:54.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.74,0:01:00.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I joined the Guild just so \Nthat I could challenge you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.45,0:01:01.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I am Poe!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:04.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Detective and master of intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.04,0:01:07.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You defeated me six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.62,0:01:09.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Your rant's making me sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.38,0:01:10.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.84,0:01:12.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,This is a detective game!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:19.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Read this detective novel I've prepared for you, \Nand determine the identity of the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:21.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,One point docked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:25.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have become a detective \Nif you were content with novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.52,0:01:28.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I expected that reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.60,0:01:34.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,How about, if you win, \NI tell you the Guild's weakness?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.45,0:01:41.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,How to capture the Guild base,\NMoby Dick, the floating fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.41,0:01:42.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,One point granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.91,0:01:46.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,But why such a silly challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.58,0:01:50.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild's operations are barbaric \Nand unbearably boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.75,0:01:54.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing humanity \Nought to have interest in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:58.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,is your gift, Ultra Deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:00.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:02.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Five points granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:04.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:09.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,The story begins like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:11.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,One night, once upon a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:15.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,a band of visitors were trapped \Nin a mansion due to a snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:20.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,On the night of their stay,\N the protagonist, a private detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.61,0:02:25.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,is awakened by a strange noise \Ncoming from one of the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.42,0:02:33.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,This is my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:36.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The ability to suck a reader into a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:40.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to the house of tragedies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.49,0:02:52.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The protagonist opens the door \Nwith a key only he possesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,What he saw there...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:00.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,A victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:04.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,The two windows were sealed, and no one \Ncould have entered or left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:10.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Two doors, and a matching key.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:18.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:20.55,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:21.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:22.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:24.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:27.51,Stray Dogs - Default,He's not dead?!,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The door...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.77,0:03:37.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,He said it was a serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.44,0:03:43.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we need to find the \Nmurderer, or we'll be killed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:51.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain in the ass, that ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:54.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse and the blood are \Ndisgustingly convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:04:00.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention my ability, \NThou Shalt Not Die, doesn't work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:03.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is the caretaker of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:05.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Cause of death is hemorrhagic shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:07.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,No weapon, no fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:08.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:11.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It's a textbook impossible murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:12.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,A locked room with no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:15.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Clearly the victim of a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:18.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,How did the killer leave the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:21.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You're having a surprisingly \Nhard time with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:23.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to do your usual thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:25.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:29.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,They were special glasses \Nthat the boss gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:32.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I need them to start my special ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:37.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Also, your healing ability \Nwouldn't work on that dying man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:42.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, in this world, \Nmy Ultra Deduction won't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:45.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it's going to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:52.98,Stray Dogs - Italics,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Rampo-san doesn't realize that he's an \Nordinary person without any special abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.52,0:04:58.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about we investigate \Ncarefully and reason our way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:04:59.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Too much work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:04:59.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:00.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.73,0:05:05.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Investigating and making inquiries is the \Nwork of detectives, not {\i1}master{\i0} detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.04,sign_9788_92_Kurosaki,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.04,sign_9788_93_tl__can_t_read__,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Convicted of Blackmail
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.04,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:17.92,sign_9837_95_Ukai,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Ukai
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:17.92,sign_9837_96_Magazine__Report,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Trashy Magazine\N Reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:16.79,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.79,0:05:17.92,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.04,sign_9906_99_Reida,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Reida
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.04,sign_9906_100_Student,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Student
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.04,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.30,sign_9957_101_The_Boss,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Proprietor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.30,sign_9957_102_Royalty,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Well-Bred \NYoung Lady, \NTraveling Alone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:23.30,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I under suspicion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:26.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have an alibi for the \Ntime of the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:28.55,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I was sleeping in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:32.35,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,I was chopping firewood in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:37.39,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking up the curse of the mansion, \NPluto, the one-eyed cat, in the study. {????? should this be "curse of the mansion's one-eyed cat, Pluto, in the study"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:39.65,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to explain myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:41.71,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:43.11,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:48.99,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:53.79,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the caretaker's room to see if\N I could find some clothes that fit me better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:58.00,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it was the curse of the one-eyed \Ncat depicted in the painting in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:06:00.71,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,This is a trick involving strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:04.21,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,The key to the locked room was \Ninside the victim's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:07.80,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,The single matching key was \Nnever used until right before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:14.47,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,The suspect killed the caretaker, took the key,\N and locked the room from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.48,0:06:21.86,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Later, the suspect used a string to return \Nthe key to the pocket under the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:25.15,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,He cut the string, collected it, \Nand disposed of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:27.03,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,How's that, detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:28.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No, rhetorical questions are rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:34.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:37.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The key is too thick to fit under the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:41.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse was on its back,\N and the key was in his hip pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:43.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You could have figured that out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:48.76,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then the murderer removed \Nthe iron bars on the window, left the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:51.89,Stray Dogs - Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,used tools to return the\N iron bars, and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.89,0:06:55.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's snowing so hard \Noutside that you can't even see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:59.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't wet near the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.73,0:07:04.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You're killing it, Rampo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.21,0:07:09.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:16.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You must have had suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:18.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Your abilities as a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:23.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,But my gift has no value in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:26.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It was the boss who gave me those glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:29.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean to tell me that \Nthe boss is lying to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:34.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:36.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Not even {\i1}you{\i0} will ever solve \Nthis mystery, Rampo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:52.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,It's a supremely unusual meta-mystery \Nwritten specifically for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:54.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're in the book, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never figure out the \Nkiller or how they did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:01.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:03.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,This is revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You may have forgotten, but I never will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.80,0:08:14.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,That day, when you defeated me in a battle of wits,\N I lost all reason to show my face to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:18.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,My mind wandered in an endless, dark room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:22.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,But I realized I can live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.07,0:08:29.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,If I only had the plentiful glory and\N praise you do, I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:33.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,So I will take them from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:38.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that means I have to burn you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.41,0:08:44.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,This is a serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.30,0:08:48.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,If I deliberately stay in a locked room by myself, \Nthe killer will come to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:51.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Now, come get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:05.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Yosano-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:07.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:10.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.69,0:09:13.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:13.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:14.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:23.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a piece of cake for the \Nworld's best detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.50,0:09:34.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,The Armed Detective Agency was established \Nsolely to make use of your gift, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:44.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still grateful that I was \Ninvited to the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.07,0:10:01.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,One down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.70,0:10:05.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,So long as you don't solve the mystery, \Nyou'll never return into the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:08.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Spend all eternity wandering \Nthrough my novel world!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:17.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.84,0:10:19.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.39,0:10:21.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't have solved that mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:23.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it was quite stimulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:26.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You made only one mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:28.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Challenging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.35,0:10:31.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You figured out who the killer was?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:32.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:34.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:38.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:41.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The locked room trick had \Nnothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:47.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The protagonist killed the victim, and the author \Ndeliberately omitted that part of the narration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:52.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,But the innovation in this gimmick \Nwas the mechanism by which
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.92,0:10:55.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,the murderer vanishes the \Nmoment I enter the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:11:00.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how desperately I search, \Nthe murderer no longer exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:06.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You went too far with \Nthe locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:08.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It's one thing if you were going \Nto lay the blame on someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.98,0:11:12.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,but the murderer had no reason to \Nmake such an inescapable room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:17.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,So, I figured, the murderer and \Nthe author must be in cahoots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.52,0:11:24.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The proof was in the glove left under \Nthe brick wall, used for the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.53,0:11:28.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The one the victim pointed \Nat right before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.45,0:11:30.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the second murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.33,0:11:34.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer had already \Nvanished by then, had he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.29,0:11:36.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,That one's even simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.38,0:11:39.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You just used an automatic machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:44.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,You manipulated the magnetism in the room \Nand threw a metal object at the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:47.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that's even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:48.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Anything goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:51.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,That's the second misdirection, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:53.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,There were hints everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:57.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The suspiciously state-of-the-art \Nmedical tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:12:01.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The characters, wearing clothes provided by \Nthe mansion rather than clothes of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:06.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The story is set in 2050.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:14.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The mansion is actually a rest house \Nattached to a massive, tall space elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:17.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,As complicated as a detective novel may get,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:21.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,once you figure out the author's ulterior \Nmotives, you've figured out half of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:22.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:24.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,Six years of my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.18,0:12:28.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The intellectual devices were \Nmuch more beautiful than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:29.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you've met your match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:30.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:34.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,You remember your battle against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:38.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I forget about \Na mystery that I solved?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.94,0:12:41.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,This takes me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.70,0:12:45.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,We were here, pitting our \Nminds against each other's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:49.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It was the only time another \Ndetective gave me chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.24,0:12:53.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,The first and the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:58.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to \Nyour next challenge, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.84,0:13:01.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you work really hard to \Ncome up with something good for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:08.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Poe,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll work really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:13.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to hold a celebration \Nfor you when we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:14.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:17.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,For the day the great detective \Nlearned the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:20.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,The day you discover that you aren't gifted,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:22.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,but that you use your powers of \Nobservation and deduction to—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.45,0:13:28.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You were laying out all \Nyour reasoning just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.82,0:13:30.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:32.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not doing any actual detective work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:33.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I just got lucky this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:35.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.29,0:13:43.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,I'd look stupid if I turned \Nout to be normal now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:49.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:51.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Yosano,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.99,0:13:54.98,Stray Dogs Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Poe and Rampo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:54.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No "fine, fine" either!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:59.73,Stray Dogs Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Whereabouts of the\N Skyfaring Moby Dick
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:13:59.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that we have information \Nwe can use to defeat the Guild?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.11,0:14:02.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,They're devising a plan inside right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.65,0:14:09.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,This is some amazing intel, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:11.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,It's worth its weight in gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:16.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,How would we make use of this to \Ntake down the Guild at its core?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:18.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Infiltrate with a bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:19.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,No good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.50,0:14:21.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Our communications will give us away, \Nand we'll get shot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:25.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:28.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,How about Kenji-kun from the \NGifted Special Operations Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:29.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,Leads to a stalemate in a ground battle, \Nand we'll be fighting overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:35.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:36.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Atsushi-kun, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,It could work, with Light Snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:41.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:43.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get right on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:45.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Do we end in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.48,0:14:46.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Rampo,0000,0000,0000,,At sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.40,0:14:59.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:03.46,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,You've got gall, betraying the Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:06.17,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:11.93,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,But did you really think the Guild wouldn't \Nhave countermeasures for your powerful ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:13.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.22,0:15:16.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But I had to say I was going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:19.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise he would never have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:21.69,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:23.77,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,It's not easy being the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:28.40,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,So, Chief Strategist, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:31.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Hi Ango, how're you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.95,0:15:34.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,I have some good news today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:37.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,We'll treat your injuries at the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:42.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be as good as new with \NYosano-san's healing ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.21,0:15:44.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you want in return?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.67,0:15:48.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Well, one of the detectives in the Agency \Nwas captured by the military police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.67,0:15:52.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,We want to save her before our \Ngrand battle with the Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:56.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the killer of 35.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:16:01.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told she's being kept on an unmanned \Nplane used to quarantine dangerous gifteds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:07.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,The Gifted Special Operations Division could indeed \Nmake an extrajudicial plea to grant her immunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.57,0:16:15.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,But only if the girl is truly \Na member of the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:19.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouka-chan isn't a member of the Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.95,0:16:23.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,She's not {\i1}yet{\i0}, to be exact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:27.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,There's an entrance examination you need \Nto take in order to become a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:32.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you pass the test, you aren't \Nofficially accepted as an employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.29,0:16:35.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Remember there was one for you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:45.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai-kun, I accept your offer of treatment \Nin exchange for my cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,So tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.28,0:16:53.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,When the unidentified car rammed into us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:56.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,for some reason my airbag was \Nthe only one that didn't deploy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:16:59.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Might you know the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:06.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,The entrance exam involves observing \Nthe applicant's behaviors
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:08.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,to determine whether they're \Nsuitable for the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:10.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,It's a secret test.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:17.22,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever Kyouka-chan is in danger, she seeks \Nescape by hurting or doing away with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:19.72,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,That may be her nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.51,0:17:23.89,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, she may \Nnot pass the entrance exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:27.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:31.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,The library?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.94,0:17:36.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tanizaki of the Armed Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:38.78,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:48.46,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.97,0:17:59.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,The Agency's micro-assault \Nfighter, the Night Bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:03.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pilot this and deliver \Nyou to the Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.98,0:18:06.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,A solo infiltration?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:10.90,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild is planning an \Nall-out ground attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:15.74,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,We'll sneak onto the Moby Dick while it's \Nsparsely staffed, and take control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.07,0:18:18.91,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to do all that by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.03,0:18:20.70,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,On a solo infiltration,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.95,0:18:26.54,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,a gifted with combat abilities is preferable,\N due to their ability to work under pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:31.42,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,You've also been held captive aboard the Moby Dick, \Nso you have an idea of its structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:36.92,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, even if you do fail, \Nthere's a good chance that you'll be captured alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.63,0:18:39.80,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,No one is more suited for the job than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:41.64,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.06,0:18:45.02,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Turn it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:46.98,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.35,0:18:50.10,Stray Dogs - Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're the runt of the orphanage \Nuntil the day you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.44,0:18:56.69,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've only ever regretted \Nthe things I didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:01.16,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:06.33,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Entering Moby Dick visual range.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:07.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:09.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go, Atsushi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:10.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.17,0:19:15.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,Ability: Light Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:16.26,sign_31340_321_Ability__Light_S,,0000,0000,0000,,{sign}Ability: Light Snow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.86,0:19:26.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,The Moby Dick's sensors are disabled for just \N130 seconds, while the transport helicopter docks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:30.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Tanizaki,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to hide ourselves \Nand close in during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:38.32,Stray Dogs - Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What? The pilot isn't responding?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:41.41,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps some trouble with the communicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:46.62,Stray Dogs - Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:09.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai-san, I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:12.93,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.19,0:20:14.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:15.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:22.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Where is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.48,0:20:26.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Almost everyone evacuated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:30.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that might be, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:32.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.37,0:20:34.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Of this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:38.92,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't he the one who \Ncalled down the Moby Dick?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.71,0:20:44.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,With the next attack, all of the \NGuild's enemies will be turned to ash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:46.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Along with Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.18,0:20:49.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:53.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,I presume you thought you'd attack \Nwhile there aren't many people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.98,0:20:56.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,But did you not suspect \Nthat something was off
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:21:01.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,when the Guild's main forces abandoned \Nthe Moby Dick now, of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.28,0:21:05.11,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,It would be terrible if \Nwe became collateral.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.37,0:21:09.51,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,Stage two of the Yokohama Incineration \NOperation: Moby Dick Bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:15.57,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,Once it happens, the city will be annihilated \Nthanks to the damage from the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.99,0:21:19.62,Stray Dogs - Default,John,0000,0000,0000,,And ground zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.01,0:21:22.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Is where the Agency and the \NMafia headquarters are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.79,0:21:27.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,We'll crash into the ground \Nin less than an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.81,0:21:32.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,If Moby Dick is your special ability, \Nyou should be able to stop its descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.34,0:21:36.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,You are correct that the Moby Dick\N is my special ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.78,0:21:40.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,But 70% of its capacity has \Nbeen replaced with ordinances.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.81,0:21:43.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,I no longer have the ability to control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:45.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that, Dazai-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.29,0:21:48.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,We need to abort the operation \Nand retreat immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:50.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,The operation continues as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:52.11,Stray Dogs - Italics,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:56.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Take control of the Moby Dick with \Nyour own hands and stop its descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.46,0:22:00.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one on the Moby Dick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:01.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.19,0:22:04.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,You predicted this situation, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.84,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,As a possibility, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:10.40,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,That was part of our \Nreason for choosing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:11.39,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.76,0:22:17.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,What do I need to do \Nto stop the descent?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.75,0:22:20.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to use the control terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.57,0:22:22.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the office on the highest floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.50,0:22:26.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's well guarded, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.37,0:22:29.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.55,0:22:36.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,If everyone's evacuated, \Nwhy are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.85,0:22:45.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,If the Moby Dick is to fall on foreign land and \Ncause annihilation, I reckon I ought to fall with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.10,0:22:52.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Moby Dick was a beautiful creature \Nbefore its flesh became mechanical.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.23,0:22:57.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Herman,0000,0000,0000,,Just as the Guild was in its past.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.57,0:23:03.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.83,0:23:05.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,How are you, Dazai-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.63,0:23:10.38,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.51,0:23:15.63,Stray Dogs - Italics,Dazai,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we establish an agreement with the \NMafia so they wouldn't obstruct our operations?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.22,0:23:21.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,About that agreement... I just had a \Ncall from one of the subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.56,0:23:23.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Mori,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like it'll hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.59,0:23:29.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.77,0:23:32.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Akutagawa,0000,0000,0000,,I've found you, weretiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:36.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Atsushi,0000,0000,0000,,Akutagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.52,0:23:40.01,sign_37678_384_Episode__Twenty_,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Episode \NTwenty-Three
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.52,0:23:40.01,sign_37678_385_Rashomon__The_Ti,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Rashoumon, The Tiger, \Nand The Last Emperor
